    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-03-11T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-03-11T08:00:00-05:00" n="78"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d78">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">771.00/3–1153: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Diplomatic Agent at Tangier</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_VJC1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Vincent</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tangier</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-03-11T13:00:00+00:00"
                            >March 11, 1953—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>417. Although question United States reservations to Tangier protocol (<gloss
                        target="#t_Legtel1">Legtel</gloss> 407)<note n="1" xml:id="d78fn1">Not
                        printed; it indicated that on Mar. 3 <persName corresp="#p_WWII1"
                            >Witman</persName> had indicated to the members of the Control Committee
                        the reservations of the United States to the Tangier Protocol.
                        (771.00/3–353) See <ref target="#d77">
                            <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>
                        </ref>.</note> on agenda committee control meeting March 9 discussion
                    postponed permit representatives consult their governments, French Minister
                    requested views United States Government following questions stressing his
                    government not questioning United States rights Tangier but merely seeking
                    definition United States position.</p>
                <list>
                    <item>“1. Reservations having been made long after signature what effect do
                        former have on latter?</item>
                    <item>“2. To what extent does restated position on United States Government
                        modify status American representation in body committee control? Is he
                        member ‘<hi rend="italic">ad hoc</hi>’ or does he enjoy exactly same rights
                        as his colleagues? Question is important for quorum.</item>
                    <item>“3. What is position regarding right of vote for representatives United
                        States in Assembly?</item>
                    <item>“4. We recognize present status American representation but is it <hi
                            rend="italic">de facto</hi> situation not <hi rend="italic">de
                        jure</hi>. If other powers decide once more have legations in Tangier
                        Minister of United States will then be only ‘unus inter pares’”.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_VJC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vincent</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
